data.enText: a person who has been chosen to speak or vote for sb else or on behalf of a group
a representative of the UN

data.chText: 政府中我们选举产生的代表
data.enText: our elected representatives in government
a union representative

data.chText: 这个委员会包括产业界的代表。
data.enText: The committee includes representatives from industry.
rep

data.chText: 销售代表；销售代理；代销人
data.enText: a person who works for a company and travels around selling its products
a sales representative

data.chText: 她是我们公司驻法国的销售代表。
data.enText: She's our representative in France.
a person chosen to take the place of sb else

data.chText: 他代表女王出席了庆典。
data.enText: He was the Queen's representative at the ceremony.
a person who is typical of a particular group

data.chText: 这位歌手被看作是她那一代年轻人的典型代表。
data.enText: The singer is regarded as a representative of the youth of her generation.
(in the US) a member of the House of Representatives, the Lower House of Congress; a member of the House of Representatives in the lower house of a state parliament
typical of a particular group of people

data.chText: 由500人参加的问卷调查能真正代表所有民众吗？
data.enText: Is a questionnaire answered by 500 people truly representative of the population as a whole?
containing or including examples of all the different types of people or things in a large group
a representative sample of teachers
able to be used as a typical example of sth

data.chText: 这幅画不是他在那个时期的代表作。
data.enText: The painting is not representative of his work of the period.

data.chText: 由代表组成的；代议制的

before.enText: of a system of government, etc.

data.enText: consisting of people who have been chosen to speak or vote on behalf of the rest of a group
a representative democracy

simple_means.memory_skill: represent 作…的代表 + ative 有…倾向（性质）的 → 有代表性的

ex.chText: 政府派了10位代表前往中国。
ex.enText: The government has sent ten delegates to China.

ex.chText: 保守党已经派出代表参加大会。
ex.enText: The Conservatives have sent their delegates to the conference.

synonyms.bx: 通常由选举产生或由政府、党派等指派，主要为某一群体阐述意见、进行投票选举、作决策等。

ex.chText: 我不在时，我弟弟将代理我的工作。
ex.enText: My brother will act as a deputy for me while I am away.

ex.chText: 这个公司的董事长派一名副手出席了会议。
ex.enText: The president of the company appointed a deputy to attend the meeting.

synonyms.bx: 指被上级授权具体行事、职位仅居于其下的人。

ex.chText: 他是中国驻联合国的常驻代表。
ex.enText: He is the permanent representative/delegate of China to the UN.
He once had worked as a union representative/delegate.

synonyms.bx: 通常指被推选或者被任命的代表，其职务有时是较长期的，常可与 delegate 换用。

tr: an item of information that is typical of a class or group
example: this patient provides a typical example of the syndrome
there is an example on page 10

tr: a member of the United States House of Representatives
an advocate who represents someone else's policy or purpose
example: the meeting was attended by spokespersons for all the major organs of government

tr: being or characteristic of government by representation in which citizens exercise power through elected officers and representatives
example: representative government as defined by Abraham Lincoln is government of the people, by the people, for the people
the bald eagle is representative of the United States

value.def: A representative is a person who has been chosen to act or make decisions on behalf of another person or a group of people.

example.ex: Employees from each department elect a representative.
example.tran: 每个部门的员工选举一名代表。

value.def: A representative is a person whose job is to sell a company's products or services, especially by travelling round and visiting other companies.

example.ex: She had a stressful job as a sales representative.
example.tran: 作为一名销售代表，她的工作压力很大。

value.def: A representative group consists of a small number of people who have been chosen to make decisions on behalf of a larger group.

example.ex: The new head of state should be chosen by an 87 member representative council.
example.tran: 新的国家元首应该由包括87名成员的代表委员会选出。
代议制政府的各个机构

value.tran: 由代表组成的;代议制的

value.def: Someone who is typical of the group to which they belong can be described as representative .

example.ex: He was in no way representative of dog-trainers in general.
example.tran: 他远不是一般意义上的驯狗师。
相当典型的成年人群体

example.ex: ...a process designed to ensure the representativeness of the sample interviewed.
example.tran: 为保证抽样的对象具有代表性而设计的过程

value.def: In the United States, a Representative is a member of the House of Representatives, the less powerful of the two parts of Congress.
